  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The ship, Columbus, could not sail today. As a result of this delay, they will probably not arrive in time for the opening of the World&apos;s Convention. If Garrison is present at the convention, the &quot;woman question&quot; will be brought up. Lucretia Mott is among the delegates appointed by the American Anti-Slavery Society. George Bourne is against women&apos;s rights. William Lloyd Garrison meditates on his love for his wife and children. He is distressed by the poor health of his brother James; Garrison prays that James repents. Nathaniel P. Rogers and William L. Garrison were hospitably entertained at Mrs. Truesdell&apos;s. Garrison addressed an audience of black people in Theodore S. Wright&apos;s meetinghouse.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
